-- Best Buy to Introduce Tablet to Compete With Amazon, Apple
-- B y   B r y a n   G r u l e y
-- 2012-10-17T20:25:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-17/best-buy-to-introduce-tablet-to-compete-with-amazon-apple.html
Best Buy Co. (BBY) , the world’s largest
electronics retailer, will introduce a tablet computer to
compete against  Amazon.com Inc. (AMZN) ’s Kindle and  Apple Inc. (AAPL) ’s iPad.  The Insignia Flex, which uses  Google Inc.’s (GOOG)  Android
operating system, will go on sale in Best Buy stores Nov. 11,
the Richfield, Minnesota-based retailer said. The tablet will
have a 9.7-inch screen and cost about $250, according to the
company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bryan Gruley in Chicago at 
 bgruley@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
